			"color": "5"
		},
		{
			"id": "f1ef70a4acc9cc16",
			"type": "group",
			"x": -1840,
			"y": 832,
			"width": 3048,
			"height": 400,
			"label": "PIPELINE ARCHITECTURE",
			"color": "6"
		},
		{
			"id": "35d84185c36dd975",
			"type": "group",
			"x": -1812,
			"y": -612,
			"width": 760,
			"height": 554,
			"label": "Captain  (core)",
			"color": "4"
		},
		{
			"id": "fb6e5293b76d40dd",
			"type": "group",
			"x": -1812,
			"y": -42,
			"width": 760,
			"height": 722,
			"label": "Tool Extensions",
			"color": "3"
		},
		{
			"id": "ca495344a79c77ec",
			"type": "group",
			"x": -1004,
			"y": -612,
			"width": 720,
			"height": 802,
			"label": "Safety Suite",
			"color": "1"
		},
		{
			"id": "58f43b6ada9b0984",
			"type": "group",
			"x": -1004,
			"y": 206,
			"width": 720,
			"height": 566,
			"label": "Other Extensions"
		},
		{
			"id": "59e9a1c82e059819",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -430,
			"y": -1120,
			"width": 860,
			"height": 280,
			"text": "## pi-captain\n\nPipeline orchestrator for **pi** — wire LLM steps into sequential, parallel, and pool pipelines. Each step declares its own model, tools, and temperature inline.\n\n```\npi install git:github.com/Pierre-Mike/pi-captain\n```",
			"color": "4"
		},
		{
			"id": "e7a8eecda24d127a",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1782,
			"y": -572,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## captain/\n\nPipeline orchestrator — all tools & slash commands for authoring and running Captain pipelines from TypeScript files.",
			"color": "4"
		},
		{
			"id": "edde88a88bfb6c12",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1782,
			"y": -396,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 280,
			"text": "`captain_load`       load a preset or `.ts` pipeline file\n`captain_run`        execute a pipeline with input\n`captain_status`     check progress, tokens, cost, gate results\n`captain_list`       list all defined pipelines\n`captain_generate`   generate a TypeScript pipeline on-the-fly\n`captain_validate`   validate a pipeline spec for correctness"
		},
		{
			"id": "83cdda6e7c43d4fa",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1782,
			"y": 26,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## native-web-search/\n`web_search` tool — live internet search via Anthropic's web search beta",
			"color": "3"
		},
		{
			"id": "088f5ef083d4f8b8",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1782,
			"y": 182,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## agent-loop/\n`/loop` command — repeat agent turns by goal, count, or pipeline stages"
		},
		{
			"id": "894c0415a9228809",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1782,
			"y": 338,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## refactor-loop/\n`/refactor` command — iterative analyze -> refactor -> verify cycles with `refactor_pass` tool"
		},
		{
			"id": "ebff537137b55429",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1782,
			"y": 494,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## freecad/\n`freecad_*` tools — drive FreeCAD headlessly to create and export 3D models"
		},
		{
			"id": "3c9c88f617c029f2",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": -572,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## safety-destructive-commands/\nBlocks `rm -rf`, `dd`, fork bombs and other destructive bash commands before they run",
			"color": "1"
		},
		{
			"id": "58bda2b93c2399f2",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": -396,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## safety-git-operations/\nConfirms risky git ops: `push --force`, `reset --hard`, `clean -f` and others"
		},
		{
			"id": "c30eab2ed670a866",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": -220,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## safety-network-exfiltration/\nBlocks curl-pipe-to-shell, secret leaks, and sensitive file transfers over the network"
		},
		{
			"id": "be32dd7e15f612ed",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": -44,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## safety-path-protection/\nProtects `.git/`, `node_modules/`, `.env`, SSH keys and other critical paths from writes"
		},
		{
			"id": "90719509a89e84de",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": 274,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## clear/\n`/clear` and `/reset` commands — wipe session history and reload extension state"
		},
		{
			"id": "8904909f97df5848",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": 430,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## terminal/\n`/terminal` command — open a terminal split in your editor from within pi"
		},
		{
			"id": "b719440bd4080b51",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -974,
			"y": 586,
			"width": 660,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "## zellij-tab-namer/\nAuto-renames the active Zellij tab to the current project name after each agent turn"
		},
		{
			"id": "a37223bf411263c0",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": -572,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## captain/\nGuides the LLM on pipeline authoring — when to use `sequential` vs `parallel`, gate patterns, transform strategies.",
			"color": "4"
		},
		{
			"id": "824844dd7f20fd24",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": -396,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## research-swarm/\nParallel 5-agent research with democratic scoring — 5 distinct angles, shared findings registry, argue & vote to rank.",
			"color": "5"
		},
		{
			"id": "1ce85aab86ae0b3c",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": -220,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## json-canvas/\nJSON Canvas format for Obsidian `.canvas` files — generate diagrams, validate correctness, and auto-fix geometry issues.",
			"color": "3"
		},
		{
			"id": "5b2aa136e008ca3e",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": -44,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## extension-generator/\nBuild and debug pi extensions — `registerTool()`, slash commands, event interceptors, stateful UI widgets, bash wrappers."
		},
		{
			"id": "d09f762cfc85ff45",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": 132,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## extension-testing/\nUnit tests for pure logic, integration mocks, bun smoke tests, and eval datasets for LLM-backed extensions."
		},
		{
			"id": "495535c90fdf250d",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": 308,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## skill-generator/\nGenerate new Claude Code skills following progressive disclosure principles and degrees-of-freedom matching."
		},
		{
			"id": "bd675779f0ed0267",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": 484,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## pi-ui-extension/\nBuild custom TUI footers, widgets, and overlays — themed status text, live cost bars, streaming progress loaders."
		},
		{
			"id": "f13cadb7013b07f0",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 430,
			"y": 660,
			"width": 700,
			"height": 160,
			"text": "## pi-ux-intake/\nDesign user intake flows — intercept first message, pre-fill editor, `confirm`/`select`/`input` primitives."
		},
		{
			"id": "55be0635baa58fa8",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1810,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 440,
			"height": 200,
			"text": "## Sequential\n\nSteps run one after another. Output of each step becomes `$INPUT` for the next. `$ORIGINAL` always holds the initial user message. Gates and transforms run between steps.",
			"color": "6"
		},
		{
			"id": "e6553194f82dec60",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -1354,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 400,
			"height": 200,
			"text": "## Parallel\n\nAll steps run concurrently with the same input. Results are merged by the configured merge strategy when all workers finish.",
			"color": "6"
		},
		{
			"id": "7224b834eebb804a",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -938,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 420,
			"height": 200,
			"text": "## Pool\n\nA queue of N items processed by M concurrent workers. Each worker runs the same step spec. Useful for batch processing and parallel map operations.",
			"color": "6"
		},
		{
			"id": "79c0609d34d54f47",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -470,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 420,
			"height": 280,
			"text": "## Gates\n\nQuality check that runs after each step completes:\n`bunTest`   run `bun test`, pass on exit 0\n`command`   run any shell command, check exit code\n`regexCI`   match step output against a pattern\n`user`      human approval in interactive UI\n`llmFast`   use a fast LLM as quality judge",
			"color": "1"
		},
		{
			"id": "700764d486d90ee4",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -34,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 400,
			"height": 280,
			"text": "## OnFail Handlers\n\nWhat to do when a gate rejects a step's output:\n`retry(n)`   re-run the step up to n times\n`skip`       skip and continue to next step\n`warn`       log a warning, continue pipeline\n`abort`      halt the entire pipeline immediately",
			"color": "2"
		},
		{
			"id": "f0e83a3d701c0765",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 382,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 400,
			"height": 260,
			"text": "## Transforms\n\nShape step output before passing it downstream:\n`full`           pass complete output as-is\n`summarize(n)`   compress to n tokens via LLM\n`extract(re)`    extract matching portion via regex",
			"color": "3"
		},
		{
			"id": "692b35d9bf63935e",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 798,
			"y": 902,
			"width": 380,
			"height": 300,
			"text": "## Builtin Presets\n\n`githubPrReview`         GitHub PR review\n`reqDecompose`           requirements decomposition\n`reqDecomposeAi`         AI-powered req. decomposition\n`requirementsGathering`  requirements gathering\n`researchSwarm`          5-agent parallel research\n`specTdd`                spec-driven TDD\n`showcase`               self-contained demo",
			"color": "4"
		},
		{
			"id": "8e817aa4aada0a51",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 400,
			"y": 1272,
			"width": 760,
			"height": 140,
			"text": "**Install (project-local):** `pi install -l git:github.com/Pierre-Mike/pi-captain`\n**Install (global):** `pi install git:github.com/Pierre-Mike/pi-captain`\nUse `pi config` to toggle individual extensions and skills on/off after install.",
			"color": "4"
		}
	],
